{"id":"hocking-hills-scenic-byway","generatedAt":"2026-07-12T01:11:51.097Z","designation":"National Scenic Byway","parkCode":null,"source":{"roadArticle":"Ohio State Route 664","revisionId":1326030022,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ohio_State_Route_664"},"attribution":{"license":"CC BY-SA 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/","articleUrl":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ohio_State_Route_664","text":"Route, junction, and history details adapted from the Wikipedia article \"Ohio State Route 664\", by Wikipedia contributors, licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0."},"sources":[{"name":"Wikipedia","src":"wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ohio_State_Route_664","revisionId":1326030022,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-12T01:11:51.097Z"},{"name":"Federal Highway Administration — National Scenic Byways","src":"fhwa","url":"https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/byways","retrievedAt":"2026-07-12T01:11:51.097Z"},{"name":"OpenStreetMap contributors (ODbL)","src":"osm","url":"https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright","retrievedAt":"2026-07-12T01:11:51.097Z"}],"endpoints":{"from":"Benton Township, OH","to":"Rushville, OH","via":["Logan, OH","Rush Creek Township, OH"]},"itinerary":[{"seq":1,"place":"Benton Township","state":"OH","kind":"terminus","mileFromStart":0,"toNextMi":15,"note":"The drive begins here","control":["Laurelville","Athens"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":2,"place":"Logan","state":"OH","kind":"town","mileFromStart":15,"toNextMi":11.3,"note":"Junction toward Lancaster & Athens","control":["Lancaster","Athens"],"lat":39.57665,"lng":-82.52211,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":3,"place":"Rush Creek Township","state":"OH","kind":"town","mileFromStart":26.3,"toNextMi":5.6,"note":"","control":["New Lexington","Lancaster"],"lat":39.57665,"lng":-82.52211,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":4,"place":"Rushville","state":"OH","kind":"terminus","mileFromStart":31.9,"toNextMi":null,"note":"The drive ends here","control":["Somerset","Lancaster"],"lat":39.4399,"lng":-82.5639,"src":"wikipedia"}],"history":{"paragraphs":["SR 664 was designated in 1937. The original routing of this highway included the current stretch of SR 374 from its southern terminus at SR 56 southeast of South Bloomingville to the eastern intersection between SR 374 and SR 664, and the present routing of SR 664 from that point to its northern terminus at SR 256 north of Rushville. After just one year, SR 664 was shortened when its southern terminus was moved to the present eastern junction of SR 374 and SR 664. This occurred as a result of SR 374 being extended from that location south along the former section of SR 664 to its present southern endpoint at SR 56.","In 1946, SR 664 took on the shape that it has today. From the eastern SR 374/SR 664 junction, SR 664 was routed west concurrent with SR 374 for a distance of more than 2 miles (3.2 km), then southwesterly along a previously un-numbered roadway to South Bloomingville and its present southern terminus at SR 56.","Starting in 2011, SR 664 (along the concurrency with SR 374) was rerouted to a new alignment near the Old Man's Cave area of Hocking Hills State Park. The realignment was needed to reduce the conflict between traffic on the road and pedestrians in the vicinity of the park. The one-mile-long (1.6 km) realignment opened by January 2013. The interchange at US 33 in Logan, originally a standard diamond interchange with an increasing accident rate, was reconstructed to be a double-roundabout or dumbbell interchange that opened on December 4, 2013. This type of interchange is the first constructed and opened in Ohio."],"sourceSection":"History","src":"wikipedia"},"highlights":[{"n":"Rushville","d":"The drive ends here","q":"Rushville","lat":39.76444444,"lng":-82.43027778,"src":"wikipedia"}],"references":[{"n":1,"text":"\"Division of Planning - Office of Technical Services - Destape files\". ODOT. July 16, 2013. Retrieved February 3, 2014. See Hocking County, Fairfield County","url":"http://www.dot.state.oh.us/Divisions/Planning/TechServ/TIM/Pages/DESTAPE.aspx"},{"n":2,"text":"Ohio Department of Transportation. \"Technical Services Straight Line Diagrams\". Retrieved February 18, 2011.","url":"http://www.dot.state.oh.us/Divisions/Planning/TechServ/TIM/Pages/Straight-Line-Diagrams.aspx"},{"n":3,"text":"Official Ohio Highway Map (MrSID) (Map). Cartography by ODOH. Ohio Department of Highways. 1936. Retrieved February 20, 2011.","url":"http://www.dot.state.oh.us/Divisions/TransSysDev/Innovation/prod_services/Documents/StateMaps/otm1936a.sid"},{"n":4,"text":"Official Ohio Highway Map (MrSID) (Map). Cartography by ODOH. Ohio Department of Highways. 1937. Retrieved February 20, 2011.","url":"http://www.dot.state.oh.us/Divisions/TransSysDev/Innovation/prod_services/Documents/StateMaps/otm1937a.sid"},{"n":5,"text":"National Highway System: Ohio (PDF) (Map). Federal Highway Administration. December 2003. Archived from the original (PDF) on October 16, 2008. Retrieved February 19, 2011.","url":"https://web.archive.org/web/20081016165827/http://www.fhwa.dot.gov/planning/nhs/maps/oh/oh_Ohio.pdf"},{"n":6,"text":"Official Ohio Highway Map (MrSID) (Map). Cartography by ODOH. Ohio Department of Highways. 1938. Retrieved February 20, 2011.","url":"http://www.dot.state.oh.us/Divisions/TransSysDev/Innovation/prod_services/Documents/StateMaps/otm1938a.sid"},{"n":7,"text":"Ohio Highway Map (MrSID) (Map). Cartography by ODOH. Ohio Department of Highways. 1945. Retrieved February 20, 2011.","url":"http://www.dot.state.oh.us/Divisions/TransSysDev/Innovation/prod_services/Documents/StateMaps/otm1945a.sid"},{"n":8,"text":"Ohio Highway Map (MrSID) (Map). Cartography by ODOH. Ohio Department of Highways. 1946. Retrieved February 20, 2011.","url":"http://www.dot.state.oh.us/Divisions/TransSysDev/Innovation/prod_services/Documents/StateMaps/otm1946a.sid"}],"routeLine":[[39.57665,-82.52211],[39.57637,-82.52299],[39.57584,-82.52447],[39.57566,-82.52523],[39.57569,-82.52611],[39.57556,-82.52